{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1a46966b-defc-47f6-9f6b-6a365acf68c2","content":"Could you clarify what you mean by \"file system wrapper\"? Your code already uses `IFileSystem` from `System.IO.Abstractions`, which is itself the abstraction layer. Are you looking for:\n\n1. **A custom service/facade** that wraps `IFileSystem` with higher-level methods (e.g., adding logging, error handling, retry logic)?\n2. **A simpler custom interface** that only exposes the file system methods you actually need?\n3. **A test/mock helper** for unit testing classes that depend on `IFileSystem`?\n\nSomething else? A bit more detail on what the wrapper should do will help me generate exactly what you need.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"71f9ce00-dd03-47d5-b1ab-cf4cfff6aa61","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a simple C# codebase using `System.IO.Abstractions` with `IFileSystem`. They want me to generate a file system wrapper. \n\nBut wait - `System.IO.Abstractions` already IS the wrapper/abstraction. What could they mean by \"generate a file system wrapper\"?\n\nLooking at this more carefully - they say \"My code already uses IFileSystem from System.IO.Abstractions everywhere\" and they want a \"file system wrapper.\" \n\nI think they might want a concrete implementation/wrapper class that wraps the real file system - i.e., a class that implements `IFileSystem` or provides a simplified facade over file system operations. But `System.IO.Abstractions` already provides `FileSystem` as the concrete implementation.\n \nOr maybe they're looking for a custom service layer that wraps `IFileSystem` to expose only the specific operations their application needs, rather than the full interface. That would make sense - a domain-specific wrapper that simplifies their codebase by hiding the complexity of `System.IO.Abstractions` behind a more focused API tailored to their actual use cases.\n\nI should ask what specific methods they need exposed and what additional functionality they want the wrapper to provide beyond what `IFileSystem` already offers.","outputTokens":559,"requestId":"0420:1DAD83:407DB2:4C397E:69E828A0"},"id":"269b5c92-babf-45ab-b0bf-845c30dc33f6","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:47:25.697Z","parentId":"5ec6d466-5245-4dea-9ea1-6972725f8904"}
